kirk and former senate postal clerk fred rader 
gunter who lost to paula hawkins in the 1980 senate race 
raised 1 million within six weeks of announcing and opponents 
noted he took at least 160000 from the insurance industry he 
regulates mackay campaign manager greg farmer called gunters 
department a saga of sleaze 
the early democratic frontrunner former gov reubin askew quit 
the race in may saying running for office had become too expensive 
democrats acknowledge that their crowded field and likely runoff 
may hurt their prospects in november 
i dont think itll be an easy race but i think its 
winnable said state democratic chairman charles whitehead 
