<TEXT>
with 25000 firefighters in the west the 
logistics of supplying all of them is staggering say officials of 
the federal center established to do just that 
as of monday the boise interagency fire center has sent out 
50000 pairs of fire retardant gloves 25445 pairs of flameproof 
trousers and nearly 32000 paper sleeping bags 
it also has distributed 41607 canteens 30984 shirts nearly 
3000 cans of foot powder 15 pocket dictionaries and for 
firefighters internal blazes 182 bottles of antacid 
the center established in 1965 is responsible for dispatching 
firefighters aircraft and supplies to state and federal agencies 
throughout the country 
more than 67000 fires burning a record of more than 36 
million acres have been reported in the united states this year 
the previous record was 32 million acres in 1985 
this has been a very long fire season said arnold hartigan 
public affairs officer it began early in june and now almost 
three months later it shows no signs of letting up 
labor day was typical of the workload while about 10 people 
might be on duty on a normal labor day hartigan said about 150 
were working at center this year 
the fire management center is made up of personnel from the 
bureau of land management the forest service national park 
service bureau of indian affairs and the us fish and wildlife 
service 
through the weekend the center has sent out 23 million pounds 
of supplies valued at about 14 million 
along with the other necessities hartigan said 103000 message 
forms have been distributed to firefighters 
this is the government and we do need to keep up on our 
paperwork he said 
