official duty since he suffered the aneurysm july 23 while 
vacationing in gatlinburg tenn 
the archbishop underwent surgery july 25 at cincinnatis good 
samaritan hospital where neurosurgeons sealed the ruptured artery 
and rerouted the brains blood supply to avoid a possible fatal 
recurrence he was released from the hospital aug 11 
an aneurysm is a sac formed in the wall of an artery and is 
blamed on a congenital weakness in the arterial wall 
pilarczyk refused interviews tuesday but is to hold a news 
conference thursday 
his doctors said pilarczyk gave them approval to be the first in 
cincinnati to use an experimental drug which doctors said may have 
helped save his life by possibly preventing arterial spasms that 
can occur even after surgery the drug called nicardipine relaxes 
the arterial wall and prevents spasms doctors said 
pilarczyk is spiritual leader of about 550000 catholics in the 
