<TEXT>
dictator josef stalin went unattended by doctors 
for at least 14 hours after he suffered a fatal stroke in 1953 
because his security chief refused to let anyone summon physicians 
according to an estonian newspaper 
sovietskaya estonia said in an edition that arrived in moscow 
tuesday that stalins bodyguards found him incapacitated on the 
floor of his country residence but lavrenti beria insisted stalin 
was sleeping 
no one dared contradict beria and stalin was left unattended 
until the next day the newspaper reported in its sunday edition 
beria became head of the secret police in 1938 and carried out 
bloody purges during the stalin era 
the newspaper said its report was based partly on an account 
recently given to it by a retired security officer a t rykov 
who claimed he was present at stalins dacha or country home when 
stalin died 
stalin had ruled since 1924 little official information was 
given about his death in march 1953 and his final days have been a 
mystery to historians 
sovietskaya estonia gave this version 
stalin probably died several days before march 5 1953 the day 
his death was announced and that given officially as the date of 
death 
stalin died at his dacha and not in the kremlin as official 
reports said 
an autopsy showed stalin suffered a series of small strokes in 
his final years that affected parts of the brain responsible for 
psychotic activities 
it took more than six months to embalm and preserve the body 
before it was put on public display 
the newspaper said rykov who retired as a major served as a 
guard at stalins dacha and recently entered the papers editorial 
department and offered to tell his story 
he could talk for hours about the leader of the people 
saving every little fact in his memory the report said 
it quoted rykov was as saying stalin went to bed at 4 am on 
march 1 1953 after guests had left 
in the afternoon guards noticed there was no movement in 
stalins study or other rooms but at 630 pm a light was turned 
on in the study and in the hall rykov said according to the 
newspaper 
it quoted him as saying no one summoned the guards who became 
concerned when one went in to deliver a letter stalin was lying on 
the carpet in the dining room having obvious difficulties in 
saying anything other guards came into the room and carried stalin 
into the largest hall it could be seen that he was cold and he 
probably was on the floor three to four hours without any help 
the account said beria and georgi m malenkov a close aide who 
briefly succeeded stalin as top leader arrived at 3 am on march 
2 after beria telephoned instructions that no one was to say 
anything about stalins condition 
after seeing the unconscious leader beria insisted the guards 
had panicked and that stalin was simply sleeping according to 
the report 
doctors finally were summoned apparently by nikita s 
khrushchev who won a power struggle to become communist party chief 
later in 1953 and they arrived between 9 am and 10 am 
the doctors were so nervous they could not even take off 
stalins shirt rykov was quoted as saying it had to be cut 
through with scissors the diagnosis was brain hemorrhage 
treatment was attempted but it was not surgical what surgeon 
could take responsibility for stalins life especially when beria 
frightened everybody asking whether they could guarantee that 
stalins life could be preserved 
beria was arrested in july 1953 and charged with conspiracy 
against the state after a secret trial he and six alleged 
accomplices where shot in december 1953 
the newspaper article described the evening of march 5 1953 
when ss debov who had embalmed the body of soviet founder 
vladimir lenin was summoned 
one of stalins cars took debov to stalins postmortem 
examination which showed some irreversible changes localized in 
parts of the brain responsible for psychotic activities which were 
caused by a number of small hemorrhages rykov said 
stalins funeral was held on march 9 and the body carried to the 
tomb the mausoleum was closed for more than eight months for a 
more permanent embalming procedure 
on nov 17 1953 the mausoleum was opened for the people with 
lenin and stalin lying together the newspaper said 
it reported the identical coffins remained side by side until 
825 pm on oct 31 1961 when soldiers took stalins remains to 
a plain gravesite nearby but outside the kremlin wall 
khrushchev had begun his campaign against what he called the 
cult of stalin 
</TEXT>
