<TEXT>
democratic presidential nominee michael dukakis 
was grounded tuesday and had to cancel an ohio campaign stop after 
the federal aviation administration sprung a surprise inspection of 
his chartered airplane and found safety problems with it 
dukakis spent much of tuesday afternoon at chicagos ohare 
international airport he canceled a trip to columbus ohio and 
returned to boston on the press plane that accompanies his campaign 
after landing in boston dukakis told reporters that the timing 
of the faas spot inspection was very curious but declined to 
comment further 
campaign press secretary dayton duncan said the inspection could 
have been performed overnight and added were looking forward to 
the moment in january when he gets to name the faa administrator 
the misfortunes with campaign aircraft continued despite the 
grounding as s reporters and staff disembarked from the media 
plane a coneshaped section at the rear fell to the ground 
exposing the open cabin inside 
the planes pilot who had invited dukakis to sit in the jump 
seat of the cockpit during the landing blamed the mishap on 
someone inside the plane who he said pulled a cable jettisoning the 
tail cone 
the pilot who declined to give his name said the tail cone 
could not have come off during an actual flight 
the boeing 737 that the candidate and his campaign staff had 
been using was taken out of service by presidential airways after 
an faa inspector cited at least four problems with it 
joan fudala a spokeswoman for presidential airways called the 
problems a couple of minor items that were corrected during the 
day she said the plane was expected to fly to boston and rejoin 
the dukakis campaign 
the faa said it did not actually ground the jet but pointed out 
the problems including eight inches of peeling metal skin on a 
wing flap and a cabin door that would not seal properly 
the captain elected to delay the flight so those could be 
fixed said ms fudala from the airlines headquarters in 
herndon va 
the faa called the inspection routine but duncan questioned why 
the aircraft which had been at ohare since monday could not have 
been examined earlier 
our plane has been parked here since last night and surely if 
our plane needed to be inspected it would have been more convenient 
for us to have it done last night not 15 minutes before we were 
supposed to leave he said 
he said the campaign had been told that the order to inspect the 
plane came from officials at the faas regional office in chicago 
mort edelstein a spokesman at the regional faa office said the 
agency is inspecting all candidate and press planes once every 
two weeks on average 
in washington faa spokesman fred farrar said the ramp 
inspection which consists of close visual inspection of the 
exterior and interior of the aircraft was similar to those 
conducted in recent weeks on other planes chartered by the two 
presidential candidates 
he said that between aug 23 and aug 26 the faa inspected two 
aircraft belonging to the dukakis campaign and three hired by the 
bush campaign including one carrying gop vice presidential 
candidate dan quayle bush travels on air force two which is 
closely inspected by the military 
these were all ramp inspections it is part of a deliberate 
program to keep close tabs on the safety of aircraft used by the 
political candidates said farrar 
according to the faa the problems found on the presidential 
airways jet were a delamination of metal skin on a wing flap a 
bent stallwarning vane the device that measures wind flow and 
triggers a warning if the aircraft is about to stall 
pressurization problems with the leftfront cabin door and 
improperly working floor proximity lights 
</TEXT>
