<TEXT>
two cosmonauts returned safely to earth early 
wednesday after their descent was aborted twice because of a system 
malfunction and their food and oxygen began to run out the 
official soviet news agency reported 
tass reported that abdul ahad mohmand the first afghan in 
space and his soviet crewmate vladimir lyakhov touched down at 
450 am moscow time 850 pm edt tuesday in soviet central 
asia 
both cosmonauts feel fine after the landing tass said 
the agency said their soyuz tm5 space capsule landed 99 miles 
southeast of dzhezkazgan a town on the steppes of the republic of 
kazakhstan in soviet central asia the town is about 1365 miles 
southeast of moscow 
soviet news reports earlier had said neither cosmonaut was in 
immediate danger but that the situation soon could become critical 
accident the engine worked 60 seconds and shut off a 
violation of the stabilization regime lyakhov told mission 
control in an exchange reported by the government newspaper 
izvestia 
lyakhov 47 is a military pilot who has flown in space twice 
before and mohmand 29 is an afghan air force pilot 
lyakhov mohmand and soviet doctor valery polyakov were launched 
into space aug 29 and boarded the orbiting mir space station two 
days later polyakov remained aboard but lyakhov and mohmand 
undocked the soyuz at 255 am moscow time 655 pm monday edt 
for the trip home 
polyakov stayed on the mir to monitor the health of two other 
cosmonauts who have been in space for more than eight months 
james oberg a us expert on the soviet space program who is 
familiar with the soyuz tm5 design had said tuesday that time was 
running out 
if they cannot make the burn tonight to push them back into 
the atmosphere they will probably only live another 24 to 48 hours 
before the carbon dioxide building in the capsule will kill them 
oberg said in an interview with the associated press in houston 
officials of the us national aeronautics and space 
administration said nasa volunteered help but the soviets declined 
saying they had a technical problem but that no assistance was 
needed 
the north american aerospace defense command in colorado said 
the soyuz had split into at least two parts a normal procedure for 
reentry 
we are tracking two pieces associated with tm5 said maj 
alex mondragon a norad spokesman the capsule was in an orbit 226 
miles by 206 miles and the ships living compartment was circling 
earth 234 miles at the highest point and 155 miles at the lowest 
the soyuz capsule is designed for trips to and from space not 
for long flights 
izvestia and tass earlier reported that life support systems on 
the globeshaped capsule were designed to last two days meaning 
that had the cosmonauts not been able to descend they would have 
been in jeopardy by thursday morning 
according to the soviet space official however the cosmonauts 
could have stretched supplies of oxygen water and food for up to a 
week after that the capsule would be like a lone boat in the 
ocean he said speaking on condition of anonymity 
he did not explain how the air supply could be extended 
the capsule would have landed in china had the descent not been 
aborted the space official said contingency landing sites in 
general were not desirable because no proper ground crews would be 
there 
an izvestia article under the headline anxious hours in 
space reported this exchange between mission control and the 
cosmonauts 
how are things with food a mission controller asked 
there is no food said lyakhov 
but in the accident reserves the controller asked 
there is some but why touch it we will endure lyakhov 
said 
tass said the cosmonauts are in for difficult hours in orbit 
until the designated time of landing 
