big dreams in a small town rca restless heart 
 
the problem with this kind of countrybycommittee approach is 
that by the time everyone gets through the result is much like a 
modernday political platform it sounds nice enough and it wont 
offend anybody but its nothing to inspire the masses 
with big dreams in a small town restless heart gives us an 
album with 12 songwriters seven producers five vocalists nine 
songs and as a result no focus 
these five former nashville session players have lodged 
themselves firmly in the alabamaoak ridge boys league with mellow 
harmonies and professional musicianship but while those groups 
have managed to meld into a distinctive identity restless heart 
too often sounds like that staple of oldstyle country music shows 
the band playing a couple of tunes before the star takes the 
stage 
the bluest eyes in texas the current hit off this 
