the family has a history of buying troubled businesses and then 
waiting for a turnaround and the profit that follows 
their fortune dates back to texas wildcatter sid richardson who 
made a series of successful oil strikes richardson never married 
and left some of his millions to his partner and nephew perry bass 
perrys four sons each inherited 28 million and they combined 
assets to form bass brothers enterprises which built up the family 
wealth through shrewd investments in 1968 perry a competitive 
sailor handed over the business to son sid 
all educated at yale university the bass brothers have been 
described as atypical texas tycoons with a conservative style and 
quiet manner 
after starting his business career with wells fargo bank robert 
m bass returned to texas in 1974 to a spot at bass brothers 
enterprises 
tales of rivalries among the four brothers surfaced in recent 
years and in 1983 robert broke away and formed robert m bass 
group to pursue deals on his own 
the savings and loan deal announced monday is just the latest in 
a series for bass in recent months 
he bought the westin hotel chain from allegis corp for 153 
billion then in march sold the plaza hotel in manhattan for 410 
million to developer donald trump 
