groups administrative fund said its chief delegate lindenberg 
sette 
the shortfall in the pricestabilization fund would also leave 
the organization unable to finance a proposed new stockpiling 
scheme aimed at supporting prices now at their lowest for seven 
years 
operating costs for 198889 are estimated at 23 million the 
organization estimates it will have only 10 million to 12 million 
on hand when the new cocoa year starts oct 1 
the organization may sell cocoa from its current stockpile of 
250000 metric tons to meet the budget shortfall the 
organizations secretariat has drawn up plans to sell 10000 tons 
in 1989 and 15000 in 198990 
